1
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:26,220
(Game Notice)
Welcome to the immersive simulation.

2
00:00:26,980 --> 00:00:33,140
Welcome to the open-world social
deduction game, Door of Truth.

3
00:00:33,140 --> 00:00:36,020
You'll enter the game world as a player

4
00:00:36,020 --> 00:00:38,740
and begin your character's adventure.

5
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:41,480
This game contains four dungeons.

6
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,720
(Four dungeons)
In each dungeon,

7
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:45,800
(Character)
you'll unlock a brand-new character,

8
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,920
experience a different life,

9
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:49,680
and meet the NPCs.

10
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,760
Through exploration and interaction,

11
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,880
you'll gradually uncover
each dungeon's unique story.

12
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,000
Solve the case

13
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,480
and find the killer.

14
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:59,200
(Four dungeons complete)
Complete all four dungeons

15
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,160
to achieve the clear condition

16
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,800
(Clear achievement)
and unlock the hidden ending.

17
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,480
Each dungeon

18
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,600
(Case 1, Case 2)
may contain one

19
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,160
or more cases.

20
00:01:07,160 --> 00:01:08,400
(Random role: Detective or Suspect)
Once a case begins,

21
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,400
players will be randomly
assigned as detectives

22
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,360
or suspects.

23
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,160
(Suspect, NPC)
The killer may be hiding

24
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,520
among the suspect players or the NPCs.

25
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:17,400
(Killer)
Choose carefully.

26
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:19,240
The killer's goal is to stay hidden

27
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:20,720
and avoid being caught.

28
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:23,400
(Killer)
Only the killer is allowed to lie.

29
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,760
(Main Quest, Evidence, Explore, Rewards)
During the case,

30
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,200
(Skill Card, Trial, Stamina, Side Quest)
players can trigger various mechanics

31
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,800
to advance the investigation.

32
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:30,800
Use them wisely,

33
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,400
and you might get a breakthrough.

34
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,800
(Suspect, Killer, NPC)
When the case ends,

35
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,520
it's time to vote for the killer.

36
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,680
If the killer is identified,

37
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,120
(Correctly voted the killer)
players who voted correctly

38
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,200
will each receive a Golden Key.

39
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,840
If a player is the killer

40
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,680
(Killer, Players)
and has the lowest vote count,

41
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:48,200
(Killer's vote, Players)
that killer also receives a Golden Key.

42
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,960
(Players)
Golden Keys will be tallied

43
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:52,560
at the end of each world.

44
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,920
(Skill Cards)
They can be redeemed for Skill Cards.

45
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,860
(Gentle Reminder All persons, backgrounds,)
Player, please confirm

46
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:58,840
(and descriptions are fictional)
the game rules.

47
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,650
(Settings and actions are setups)
Dungeon loading is almost complete.

48
00:02:00,650 --> 00:02:02,690
(All photos and videos)
Get ready to dive in.

49
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:04,010
(are authorized [GenAI included])
Start deducing.

50
00:02:04,010 --> 00:02:04,340
(Safety measures were taken
during shooting. Don't try this at home)

51
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:04,780
(Parental supervision required
for underage viewers)

52
00:02:04,780 --> 00:02:05,860
(Loading)

53
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:10,700
(Loading)

54
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:13,220
(Dungeon Pass)

55
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:19,380
(The Truth)

56
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:24,460
=The Truth (Season 4)=

57
00:02:24,460 --> 00:02:25,300
(Starlight Cafe)

58
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:25,980
(DIY Mixing Area)

59
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:26,620
(Starlight Cafe)

60
00:02:27,340 --> 00:02:32,020
(Coffee)

61
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,800
How do you win this?

62
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,720
I don't think you can.

63
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,280
That's it.

64
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,120
That's all.

65
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,440
Arm workout.

66
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,120
Yeah.

67
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,640
How'd you meet Mei?

68
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,360
We...

69
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:54,240
We always got coffee at the same cafe.

70
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,960
So, at the cafe?

71
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:57,720
Morning, everyone.

72
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:58,640
How is it?

73
00:02:58,640 --> 00:02:59,480
Sleep okay?

74
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,560
Everybody sleep all right?

75
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,480
Not bad.

76
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:03,760
So...

77
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,160
Yesterday was puppet theme.

78
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,000
(Post-apocalyptic theme begins 7 April, 12AM)
Today's post-apocalyptic day.

79
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:07,960
Yep.

80
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:10,560
(#OOTD #WastelandStyle)
Everyone looks cool.

81
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,240
(#NicheStyle #AestheticArchive #2026FashionTrends)
Wasteland fits.

82
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,080
(#DoorofTruth2026WastelandFashionGuide)

83
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:12,840
(Practical apocalypse chic)

84
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:13,740
(Scrap-metal accessories:
edgy streetwear)

85
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:14,560
(Distressed denim: useful, cool)

86
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:15,120
(Armored shades, rugged edge)

87
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:15,740
(Earth tones, instant story)

88
00:03:15,740 --> 00:03:16,360
(Retro wasteland tribal)

89
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,150
(Big metal-buckle belt: tribal retro)

90
00:03:17,150 --> 00:03:18,110
(Distressed skirt over jeans,
easy layers)

91
00:03:18,110 --> 00:03:18,800
(Faux-fur collar adds bite)

92
00:03:18,810 --> 00:03:19,350
(Olive long sleeve
with a worn gray-green vest)

93
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:19,900
(Stronger wasteland tribal vibe)

94
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:20,530
(Battle-worn utility)

95
00:03:20,530 --> 00:03:21,360
(Worn gray patchwork jacket:
casual, tough)

96
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,200
(Washed wide-leg jeans
with a layered structure)

97
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,040
(Fitted tank with raw utility energy)

98
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:23,940
(Worn straps
add battle-damaged toughness)

99
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:24,540
(Post-apocalyptic punk)

100
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:25,430
(Rhinestones, sequins, chains:
fierce edge)

101
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,050
(Black combat boots
ground the shredded layers)

102
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:27,070
(Structured shoulders add punk tension)

103
00:03:27,090 --> 00:03:28,100
(Layered long skirt
sharpens the proportions)

104
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:28,820
(Distressed wasteland denim)

105
00:03:28,820 --> 00:03:29,650
(Gray base layer keeps it soft,
not messy)

106
00:03:29,650 --> 00:03:30,340
(Mid combat boots add toughness)

107
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:31,430
(Cropped denim jacket
adds retro Americana)

108
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,380
(Cargo denim pants:
loose, tough, rebellious)

109
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:32,890
(Mocha western utility)

110
00:03:32,890 --> 00:03:33,520
(Cropped tank:
casual, retro, hot-girl energy)

111
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,160
(Retro brown shoes
keep the palette soft)

112
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:34,710
(Arm cuff
with a worn black fingerless glove)

113
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:35,540
(Matching cargo pants,
worn belt, printed scarf)

114
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:36,220
(More layers, more detail)

115
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:40,840
Pose.

116
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,480
So dramatic.

117
00:03:41,940 --> 00:03:42,760
(Don't make me slap you right now)

118
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:43,280
Shut up.

119
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:44,760
Alright.

120
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,360
Yesterday, when we ended,

121
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:47,800
Mei's condition...

122
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,440
was in rough shape.

123
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:50,440
Pretty weak.

124
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:50,760
Yeah.

125
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:52,200
Is she okay?

126
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,720
She passed out.

127
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:57,440
So we let Mei rest,

128
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:58,680
and you two stayed with her.

129
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:58,920
Exactly.

130
00:03:58,920 --> 00:03:59,240
Yes.

131
00:03:59,240 --> 00:03:59,840
(Ke Coffee and Qian Jinding
stayed with Mei at the cafe all night)

132
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,360
Then why

133
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,400
are you playing games out here?

134
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,180
(Why didn't you bring Mei?)

135
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,160
We didn't want to wake her.

136
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:04,600
We waited while she slept.

137
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,560
She was exhausted.

138
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:07,040
(Somehow they still have energy)

139
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:07,520
After we took her

140
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,160
to rest,

141
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,800
we came back out.

142
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,840
We watched from outside.

143
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:12,600
Never left?

144
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,200
Yeah.

145
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:13,760
Okay.

146
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,360
The important thing is that

147
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,680
she said

148
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:18,320
there were more secrets

149
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,440
in this cafe.

150
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,120
This place is creepy.

151
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,480
There's something bigger going on.

152
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,080
Something bigger is waiting for us.

153
00:04:26,420 --> 00:04:28,000
(What else is Starlight Cafe hiding?)

154
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,360
Let's go ask her.

155
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,520
She should be rested.

156
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,240
Okay.

157
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:31,920
Come.

158
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,160
You two bring her out.

159
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:33,440
Okay.

160
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:34,600
Listen.

161
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,760
Today, I'm ready...

162
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:37,580
(Just watch)

163
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,200
Going tank mode?

164
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,320
Bold move.

165
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:41,640
(Growth speed: gigabit level)

166
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,080
Open the door.

167
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,360
(Only her attitude leveled up?)
Why so harsh?

168
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:44,720
Wait.

169
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,840
Bold doesn't mean rude.

170
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:46,680
(Watch your tone)
Listen.

171
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:47,800
Open the door!

172
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:49,360
Don't hide!

173
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,360
I know you're in there!

174
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:52,400
(Staff Lounge)
Okay.

175
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,160
Mei,

176
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,120
open the door.

177
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,380
(Please?)

178
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:56,960
(No answer)

179
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,040
(Staff Lounge)
We're coming in.

180
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,040
Mei?

181
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,160
What's wrong?

182
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:12,760
What?

183
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:13,840
What's wrong?

184
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,040
Where's Mei?

185
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,280
Mei?

186
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,000
She's gone.

187
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:19,340
(Mei isn't in the lounge?)

188
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,320
Mei's missing?

189
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,600
You sure you watched her all night?

190
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,000
I'm sure.

191
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,400
I didn't shut my eyes once.

192
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:31,980
(How did Mei vanish on their watch?)

193
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,600
I only just found her.

194
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,720
(Whose fault is that?)
You should've watched her.

195
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,040
I did watch her.

196
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,480
But you two were goofing off.

197
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,440
Why?

198
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:41,880
No!

199
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:42,520
Look at this place.

200
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:44,400
There was nowhere for anyone to sleep.

201
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,160
(You could've found a way)
Couldn't she just sleep on your lap?

202
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:46,920
That's creepy

203
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,680
if we just stare at her sleeping.

204
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,440
(Ke Coffee, played by Zhou Keyu)
While you were with her yesterday,

205
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,920
Ning was heartbroken.

206
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,440
(Me?)
He wanted to come in,

207
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,880
but felt like he had no right.

208
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,320
And you still managed to lose her.

209
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:56,920
Exactly.

210
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,040
I cheered for her downstairs all night.

211
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,520
(Fan love, physically manifested)

212
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,080
(Cola needs ice. Loving Mei takes heart)
I had my support gear and everything.

213
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:02,560
Really.

214
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,680
Yesterday, when we came in here...

215
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,160
What do you mean?

216
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,120
There's a secret passage.

217
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:09,600
A secret passage?

218
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,040
Floor plan.

219
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,080
Staff lounge.

220
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,520
There's a hidden door here, too.

221
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:15,060
(The staff-lounge hidden door
hasn't been found)

222
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,320
Behind this box.

223
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:16,920
Right?

224
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,960
Yeah. A door.

225
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,600
Let's move this.

226
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:20,720
It moves.

227
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,320
There's really a door.

228
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:24,700
(Did Mei use the secret passage?)

229
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:25,480
Look.

230
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,860
(There goes happiness)
Look at this.

231
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,440
How did this happen?

232
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:29,760
Then why'd she leave?

233
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:30,480
I finally...

234
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:30,960
No.

235
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,240
She wouldn't leave.

236
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,760
No.

237
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,240
Maybe someone took her.

238
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:37,400
(A darker possibility appears)

239
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,720
She didn't leave willingly.

240
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,180
(My Mei...)

241
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:43,920
Ke,

242
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,360
it's me.

243
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:44,840
Is that you?

244
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:45,680
It's me.

245
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:47,880
You're finally here.

246
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,840
We've searched all day for Mei.

247
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:50,700
(My Mei, how do I live without you?)

248
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,900
(Crying)

249
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,680
Okay. This is on you.

250
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,400
Go find her.

251
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:57,840
Go.

252
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,120
Let's find her together.

253
00:06:59,120 --> 00:06:59,800
(I'm responsible too)
Let's go.

254
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,120
Weren't you feeling brave today?
Come on.

255
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:03,160
Yeah. I'll show you

256
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:05,080
what one night can do.

257
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:05,940
(Showtime)

258
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,400
Careful, the lights might cut out.

259
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,840
(So much for leveling up)
Yeah, don't... Just kidding.

260
00:07:08,840 --> 00:07:09,080
Don't...

261
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:09,680
Let's go.

262
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,840
Follow her.

263
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:11,920
Through the doggy door we go.

264
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:16,180
(Staff Lounge)

265
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,440
She couldn't have left this way either.

266
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:20,860
(Ke and Qian would've noticed this door)

267
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,360
There must be another exit,

268
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:22,680
right?

269
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,440
She can exit here as well.

270
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:24,960
(Staff Lounge, VIP Room)

271
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:25,360
Also,

272
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:27,120
(Manager Tui's Office)
there's the boss's office.

273
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:28,680
And a door we haven't opened.

274
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,360
That is...

275
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:29,920
Which door haven't we opened?

276
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:30,880
Wait, the dead one is...

277
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:33,300
(Found a body)

278
