2508
01:14:15,520 --> 01:14:17,000
So we need to get inside this room.

2509
01:14:17,000 --> 01:14:18,440
(Punishment Room)
Then take this route to the body.

2510
01:14:18,500 --> 01:14:19,940
(Escape route breakdown)

2511
01:14:19,940 --> 01:14:24,540
(Enter the Punishment Room)

2512
01:14:24,540 --> 01:14:27,300
(Open the emergency exit
to the first floor)

2513
01:14:27,300 --> 01:14:29,980
(Return to the crime scene)

2514
01:14:30,060 --> 01:14:35,180
(How to enter
the third-floor Punishment Room)

2515
01:14:35,520 --> 01:14:36,160
What's this?

2516
01:14:36,160 --> 01:14:37,760
There's a note here, guys.

2517
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:44,000
You four window cleaners, be careful.

2518
01:14:44,760 --> 01:14:48,720
This glass wall was custom-made
by An Glass Factory.

2519
01:14:48,720 --> 01:14:50,640
It has four pressure points.

2520
01:14:50,640 --> 01:14:51,880
While you're working up high,

2521
01:14:51,880 --> 01:14:53,160
make sure you don't

2522
01:14:53,160 --> 01:14:56,600
kick all four pressure points hard
at the same time.

2523
01:14:56,600 --> 01:14:58,560
Otherwise, the glass will shatter.

2524
01:14:58,560 --> 01:15:00,360
You couldn't pay for it in a lifetime.

2525
01:15:04,200 --> 01:15:05,240
What's this pole for?

2526
01:15:09,280 --> 01:15:10,360
It's probably for reaching
something inside.

2527
01:15:11,560 --> 01:15:12,720
Is that the glass shield switch?

2528
01:15:12,720 --> 01:15:13,680
(Glass shield switch)
Press both buttons at the same time

2529
01:15:13,680 --> 01:15:15,320
to raise the glass shield.

2530
01:15:15,880 --> 01:15:16,960
Where's the glass shield?

2531
01:15:16,960 --> 01:15:17,720
Is it up there?

2532
01:15:17,720 --> 01:15:18,600
That's it. The glass shield.

2533
01:15:18,600 --> 01:15:19,040
That one.

2534
01:15:19,040 --> 01:15:20,500
(Glass shield)

2535
01:15:20,500 --> 01:15:21,840
(Glass shield instructions)

2536
01:15:21,840 --> 01:15:22,640
I get it now.

2537
01:15:22,640 --> 01:15:23,880
The glass is shielded right now.

2538
01:15:23,880 --> 01:15:24,440
We can't kick through it.

2539
01:15:24,440 --> 01:15:25,920
We need two poles here

2540
01:15:25,920 --> 01:15:27,120
to hold down both buttons at once.

2541
01:15:27,120 --> 01:15:27,920
(Both buttons must be pressed at once)
Then we can break the glass.

2542
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:28,840
(And break through the glass shield)
We need

2543
01:15:28,840 --> 01:15:31,400
four people over there
kicking the four glass panels.

2544
01:15:31,400 --> 01:15:31,960
(Four people kick the glass)
Then...

2545
01:15:31,960 --> 01:15:33,320
(Two people press the buttons)
Two people press these at the same time.

2546
01:15:33,880 --> 01:15:34,280
Right.

2547
01:15:34,280 --> 01:15:36,160
We should climb up from here,

2548
01:15:36,160 --> 01:15:37,520
then come down the other side.

2549
01:15:37,520 --> 01:15:37,680
Got it?

2550
01:15:37,680 --> 01:15:38,040
Yeah.

2551
01:15:38,040 --> 01:15:38,640
Come down that side.

2552
01:15:38,640 --> 01:15:40,320
Then we'll stand
behind the glass shield.

2553
01:15:40,320 --> 01:15:41,840
You two hit these switches together.

2554
01:15:41,840 --> 01:15:42,520
Once the curtain lifts,

2555
01:15:42,520 --> 01:15:43,720
we'll kick through it and get in.

2556
01:15:44,360 --> 01:15:46,280
Let me see if this pole can reach.

2557
01:15:46,280 --> 01:15:46,920
Okay.

2558
01:15:46,920 --> 01:15:47,520
Try it.

2559
01:15:47,520 --> 01:15:48,240
See if you can press it.

2560
01:15:50,760 --> 01:15:51,320
Qian, you good?

2561
01:15:53,600 --> 01:15:54,160
Okay.

2562
01:15:55,680 --> 01:15:56,280
Let's see.

2563
01:15:57,700 --> 01:16:00,260
(The glass shield rises)

2564
01:16:00,280 --> 01:16:01,440
Is that one up in the air?

2565
01:16:01,440 --> 01:16:02,780
(Up in the air)
It is.

2566
01:16:02,880 --> 01:16:03,720
I'll go take a look.

2567
01:16:03,720 --> 01:16:04,800
Hold on. I'll check it out.

2568
01:16:08,420 --> 01:16:09,540
(Be careful)

2569
01:16:26,400 --> 01:16:27,680
Guys, it's way up high.

2570
01:16:27,960 --> 01:16:28,800
This isn't gonna kill us, right?

2571
01:16:29,040 --> 01:16:30,080
You got this, Ning?

2572
01:16:30,080 --> 01:16:31,440
I'm the little bro now.

2573
01:16:31,440 --> 01:16:33,200
All four have to go at once to break it.

2574
01:16:33,200 --> 01:16:34,440
Seriously?

2575
01:16:34,440 --> 01:16:36,240
Too much slack's fine.
Too little's the problem.

2576
01:16:36,800 --> 01:16:37,560
This is so hard.

2577
01:16:37,560 --> 01:16:39,080
Go crazy or go home.

2578
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:40,920
This is way too hard.

2579
01:16:40,920 --> 01:16:42,080
I can't press it anymore.

2580
01:16:42,080 --> 01:16:43,200
It's so hard to push.

2581
01:16:44,660 --> 01:16:46,980
(Can they escape the compound?)

2582
01:16:56,560 --> 01:16:57,840
Ready? Three, two, one, go!

2583
01:16:57,840 --> 01:17:01,460
(Next episode preview)

2584
01:17:01,480 --> 01:17:02,480
Where are we?

2585
01:17:02,480 --> 01:17:03,000
Who's that?

2586
01:17:03,000 --> 01:17:04,800
How could you do something like this?

2587
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:05,440
My grandma

2588
01:17:05,440 --> 01:17:06,520
was tricked,

2589
01:17:06,520 --> 01:17:07,680
and it made her

2590
01:17:07,680 --> 01:17:09,720
give up on her treatment.

2591
01:17:09,720 --> 01:17:11,680
All my money

2592
01:17:11,680 --> 01:17:12,800
is gone.

2593
01:17:12,800 --> 01:17:14,120
It really was my face

2594
01:17:14,120 --> 01:17:14,960
and my voice

2595
01:17:14,960 --> 01:17:16,360
that took my brother away.

2596
01:17:16,360 --> 01:17:17,840
My brother developed

2597
01:17:17,840 --> 01:17:18,520
post-traumatic stress disorder.

2598
01:17:18,520 --> 01:17:20,080
Although He isn't listed here,

2599
01:17:20,080 --> 01:17:20,800
still...

2600
01:17:21,600 --> 01:17:22,720
Listen carefully.

2601
01:17:22,720 --> 01:17:24,280
Even if you run
to the ends of the earth,

2602
01:17:24,280 --> 01:17:25,440
I'll always have

2603
01:17:25,440 --> 01:17:27,240
something to hold over you.

2604
01:17:27,240 --> 01:17:28,640
You'll never get rid of it.

2605
01:17:28,640 --> 01:17:29,080
Unless...

2606
01:17:30,320 --> 01:17:31,880
I die.

2607
01:17:33,340 --> 01:17:34,160
He was killed

2608
01:17:34,160 --> 01:17:35,240
right as we were leaving.

2609
01:17:35,240 --> 01:17:35,520
Exactly.

2610
01:17:35,520 --> 01:17:36,640
You're never clearing your name.

2611
01:17:36,640 --> 01:17:37,520
In my case,

2612
01:17:37,520 --> 01:17:38,280
when you left,

2613
01:17:38,280 --> 01:17:39,240
how did you not see him?

2614
01:17:40,080 --> 01:17:40,600
Right.

2615
01:17:40,600 --> 01:17:41,880
That's impossible.

2616
01:17:41,880 --> 01:17:43,120
You two designed this together.

2617
01:17:43,120 --> 01:17:43,600
No.

2618
01:17:43,600 --> 01:17:45,440
He designed it himself.

2619
01:17:45,440 --> 01:17:47,640
I'm the only one he ever showed.

2620
01:17:47,640 --> 01:17:48,880
I was his girlfriend.

2621
01:17:48,880 --> 01:17:50,240
We were soulmates.

2622
01:17:50,240 --> 01:17:51,280
So if the killer

2623
01:17:51,280 --> 01:17:52,080
wanted to do it,

2624
01:17:52,080 --> 01:17:53,600
they had to be at the exit.

2625
01:17:53,600 --> 01:17:54,760
I think we really need

2626
01:17:54,760 --> 01:17:56,240
to question Leader Li.

2627
01:17:56,240 --> 01:17:57,360
Sit down!

2628
01:17:57,360 --> 01:17:58,560
You're definitely involved.

2629
01:17:59,040 --> 01:18:01,440
You're the only one
who fits every condition.

2630
01:18:01,440 --> 01:18:04,600
You built the profile around me.

2631
01:18:04,600 --> 01:18:06,560
You were trying to rule yourself out.

2632
01:18:06,560 --> 01:18:07,520
It was you.

2633
01:18:07,520 --> 01:18:08,800
Who cares? He's dead.

2634
01:18:08,960 --> 01:18:09,600
Shut up.

2635
01:18:10,800 --> 01:18:11,560
I touched the wall.

2636
01:18:11,560 --> 01:18:12,120
A face appeared.

2637
01:18:12,120 --> 01:18:12,720
One stab.

2638
01:19:00,680 --> 01:19:04,680
♪Come now, players all,
let the game of reason start♪

2639
01:19:04,680 --> 01:19:09,120
♪Unlock each hidden trial,
let courage spark the dark♪

2640
01:19:11,140 --> 01:19:15,300
♪Night falls slow, shadows grow,
the sleuth is lost inside the maze♪

2641
01:19:15,300 --> 01:19:19,520
♪Figures pass, lanterns sparse,
dark currents drift without a trace♪

2642
01:19:19,520 --> 01:19:23,290
♪Wind picks up, footsteps rush,
cold laughter swallowed by the dark♪

2643
01:19:23,290 --> 01:19:27,400
♪Truth concealed, the night
stands still, and nothing leaves a mark♪

2644
01:19:27,580 --> 01:19:31,700
♪An unsigned letter, coded words,
the solvers gather one by one♪

2645
01:19:31,700 --> 01:19:35,810
♪A broken game, illusion reigns,
who's hiding what they've done?♪

2646
01:19:35,810 --> 01:19:39,450
♪Hushed voices, nerves on edge,
wrapped in smoke and mirrors still♪

2647
01:19:39,450 --> 01:19:41,580
♪The next second, deeper riddles,
or the answer to the kill♪

2648
01:19:41,580 --> 01:19:45,530
♪Every piece of truth
has finally come to light♪

2649
01:19:45,770 --> 01:19:49,690
♪Unlock the mystery, turn the question,
let's begin tonight♪

2650
01:19:49,900 --> 01:19:54,050
♪Side by side, no holding back,
follow every clue to find the truth♪

2651
01:19:54,050 --> 01:19:57,610
♪The story blurs like flowers in fog,
let's begin tonight♪

2652
01:19:57,870 --> 01:20:02,520
♪Search for the vanished cipher,
trace the proof, and face the sleuth♪
